Write a short explanation (3–5 sentences) of this flow.
The user enters an email in the form. When they submit, the form sends a POST request to the server. The controller validates the email, checks for duplicates and maximum limit, then stores it in the session. The page reloads and the Blade view dynamically displays all stored emails. Users can also delete individual emails with a delete button.
Reflection Questions
Answer the following:

What is the difference between GET and POST?
asnwer: GET is used to retrieve data from the server, while POST is used to send data to the server. GET shows data in the URL, while POST hides it in the request body.
Why do we use @csrf in forms?
answer:@csrf is used to protect the application from cross-site request forgery attacks by verifying that the request is coming from a trusted source.

What is session used for in this activity?
answer:Session is used to temporarily store the list of emails so they can be displayed even after the page reloads.
What happens if session is cleared?
answer:If the session is cleared, all stored emails will be deleted and the list will become empty.